      "type": "LinguisticObject",
      "content": "This is a reproductive engraving by Christian Friedrich Boëtius (1706–1782) after a painting by Karel Dujardin (c. 1626–1678), depicting an Italianate pastoral landscape with a cow lying down and a sheep standing beside it, near a large tree. Made in Dresden in 1764, the print reproduces a painting from the collection of Christian Ludwig von Hagedorn, director of the Dresden Academy. It is listed among Boëtius's best-known works.",
